title: Grateful Dead - Live at Hampton Coliseum RSD (vinyl, FLAC)
description:
Grateful Dead
May 4, 1979
Hampton Coliseum
Hampton, VA

Live at Hampton Colisum (vinyl)

Side A
Loser
New Minglewood Blues
Don't Ease Me In
Passenger

Side B
I Need a Miracle
Bertha
Good Lovin'
Ship of Fools

Side C
Estimated Prophet
Eyes of the World

Side D
Truckin'
Stella Blue
Around and Around



This was produced as a two-disc vinyl LP, in a limited edition of 7,900 numbered copies, 
and was released on April 19, 2014, in conjunction with Record Store Day.

The May 4, 1979 concert was the band's first show at Hampton Coliseum, and their third
with then-new keyboardist Brent Mydland.
